== Avoiding GNOME deps ==
Avoiding optional GNOME support and packages will keep your system more lean and congruous.

Ensure you're using the basic desktop profile:
{{RootCmd|eselect profile list}}

You'll want the one that ends with <code>…/desktop</code> (not <code>…/gnome</code> or <code>…/kde</code>):
{{RootCmd|eselect profile set 3}}

<code>app-text/poppler</code> has a <code>qt4</code> USE flag:
{{RootCmd|mkdir /etc/portage; echo 'app-text/poppler -qt4' >> /etc/portage/package.use}}

You may also simply want to disable the flag globally:
{{RootCmd|echo 'USE{{=}}"${USE} -qt4"' >> /etc/portage/make.conf}}

<code>gnome-base/gvfs</code> has an <code>http</code> USE flag which draws in many GNOME deps you may find unnecessary:
{{RootCmd|mkdir /etc/portage; echo 'gnome-base/gvfs -http' >> /etc/portage/package.use}}

Without explicitly including <code>xfce-extra/xfce4-notifyd</code> in your <code>emerge</code> command, <code>virtual/notification-daemon</code> will draw in GNOME's <code>''x11-misc''/notification-daemon</code> instead:
{{Emerge|xfce4-meta xfce4-notifyd}}

== Installation ==
In /etc/portage/make.conf, you can add/customize this line: <code>XFCE_PLUGINS="brightness clock logout trash"</code>

The above options may change, the current list is available [http://sources.gentoo.org/cgi-bin/viewvc.cgi/gentoo-x86/profiles/desc/xfce_plugins.desc?view=markup here].

Install the complete Xfce desktop:
{{Emerge|xfce4-meta xfce4-notifyd}}

Or you can select only needed packages:
{{Emerge|xfce-base/xfwm4|xfce-base/xfce4-panel}}

