== Starting ==

=== Using <code>startx</code> ===
To start Xfce correctly with <code>startx</code>:
{{File|~/.xinitrc||<pre>
exec ck-launch-session startxfce4
</pre>}}

=== Using LightDM ===
The display manager (AKA login manager) <code>x11-misc/lightdm</code> also goes well with Xfce:
{{Emerge|lightdm}}
{{RootCmd|rc-update add xdm}}

Make sure <code>xdm</code>'s config refers to LightDM:
{{file|/etc/conf.d/xdm||<pre>
# ...
CHECKVT=7

# ...
DISPLAYMANAGER="lightdm"
</pre>}}

Upon first run you may have to select 'Xfce Session' from a drop down.

== Enabling power off and restart buttons from exit window ==

=== Configuring consolekit daemon startup ===
Check if <tt>consolekit</tt> is started:
{{Cmd|rc-status}}
If not, setup startup on boot:
{{RootCmd|rc-update add consolekit}}

=== Configuring policykit daemon ===
Example of its configuration:
{{File|/etc/polkit-1/localauthority/50-local.d/40-power.pkla||<pre>
[Local restart]
Identity=unix-group:users
Action=org.freedesktop.consolekit.system.restart
ResultAny=yes
ResultInactive=no
ResultActive=yes

[Local shutdown]
Identity=unix-group:users
Action=org.freedesktop.consolekit.system.stop
ResultAny=yes
ResultInactive=no
ResultActive=yes

[Local restart - multiple]
Identity=unix-group:users
Action=org.freedesktop.consolekit.system.restart-multiple-users
ResultAny=yes
ResultInactive=no
ResultActive=yes

[Local shutdown - multiple]
Identity=unix-group:users
Action=org.freedesktop.consolekit.system.stop-multiple-users
ResultAny=yes
ResultInactive=no
ResultActive=yes
</pre>}}
In this example permission is granted to users in group <tt>users</tt>.

